ffmpeg
------------------------------------------
FFmpeg is a complete solution to record, convert and stream audio and
video. It includes libavcodec, the leading audio/video codec library.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-15
  libSDL12-1.2.13-1
  liba52_0-0.7.4-2
  libdirac10-0.10.0-1
  libfaac0-1.26-1
  libfaad0-2.6.1-2
  libfreetype26-2.3.6-1
  libgsm0-1.0.12-1
  libimlib2-1.4.0-1
  libmp3lame0-3.97-1
  libnut0-658-1
  libschroedinger1.0_0-1.0.3-1
  libtheora0-1.0beta3-1
  libvorbis0-1.2.0-1
  libvorbisenc2-1.2.0-1
  libx264_59-20080521-1
  libxvidcore4-1.1.3-1
  zlib-1.2.3-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding devel packages)
  binutils-20080523-1
  cygport-0.3.11-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  make-3.81-1
  perl-5.10.0-4
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://ffmpeg.mplayerhq.hu/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack ffmpeg-13777-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./ffmpeg-13777-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ffmpeg-13777-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/ffmpeg-13777-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/ffmpeg-devel-13777-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libavcodec51-13777-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libavdevice52-13777-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libavfilter0-13777-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libavformat52-13777-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libavutil49-13777-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libpostproc51-13777-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libswscale0-13777-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

